question: Bob has 15 tubes of brown paint and 9 tubes of white paint. Ethan has two thirds as many tubes of brown paint as Bob, and five times as many tubes of white paint as Bob. How many tubes of paint does Ethan have?
answer:
Ethan has 15*2/3= <<15*2/3=10>>10 tubes of brown paint
Ethan has 9*5=<<9*5=45>>45 tubes of white paint
Ethan has a total of 10+45 =<<10+45=55>>55 tubes of paint
#### 55
